obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE SPECIAL COURT (TRIAL OF OFFENCES RELATING TO`
  line `TRANSACTIONS IN SECURITIES) ACT, 1992`
  line `A CT N O. 27 OF 1992`
  line `[18 th August, 1992. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the establishment of a Special Court for the trial of offences relating to`
  line `transactions in securities and for matters connected therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Forty - third Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Special Court (Trial of Offences`
  line `Relating to Transactions in Securities) Act, 1992.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 6th day of June, 1992.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “Code” means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line `( b ) “Custodian” means the Custodian appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3;`
  line `( c ) “securities” includes —`
  line `( i ) shares, scrips, stocks, bonds, debentures, debenture stock, units of the Unit Trust of India`
  line `or any other mutual fund or other marketable securities of a like nature in or of any incorporated`
  line `company or other body corporate;`
  line `( ii ) Government securities; and`
  line `( iii ) rights or interests in securities;`
  line `( d ) “Special Court” means the Special Court established under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5.`
  line `3. Appointment and functions of Custodian. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may appoint one or`
  line `more Custodians as it may deem fit for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Custodian may, on being satisfied on information received that any person has been involved`
  line `in any offence relating to transactions in securities after the 1st day of April, 1991 and on and before the`
  line `6th June, 1992, notify the name of such person in the Official Gazette.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code and any other law for the time being in force, on`
  line `and from the date of notification under sub - section ( 2 ), any property, movable or immovable, or both,`
  line `belonging to any person notified under that sub - section shall stand attached simultaneously with the issue`
  line `of the notification.`
  line `( 4 ) The property attached under sub - section ( 3 ) shall be dealt with by the Custodian in such manner`
  line `as the Special Court may direct.`
  line `( 5 ) The Custodian may take assistance of any person while exercising his powers or for discharging`
  line `his duties under this section and section 4.`
  line `4. Contracts entered into fraudulently may be cancelled. — ( 1 ) If the Custodian is satisfied, after`
  line `such inquiry as he may think fit, that any contract or agreement entered into at any time after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1991 and on and before the 6th June, 1992 in relation to any property of the person notified`
  line `under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 has been entered into fraudulently or to defeat the provisions of this`
  line `Act, he may cancel such contract or agreement and on such cancellation such property shall stand`
  line `attached under this Act:`
  line `Provided that no contract or agreement shall be cancelled except after giving to the parties to the`
  line `contract or agreement a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 2 ) Any person aggrieved by a notification issued under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 or any`
  line `cancellation made under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 4 or any other order made by the Custodian in exercise`
  line `of the powers conferred on him under section 3 or 4 may file a petition objecting to the same within thirty`
  line `days of the assent to the Special Court (Trial of Offences Relating to Transactions in Securities) Bill,`
  line `1992 by the President before the Special Court where such notification, cancellation or order has bee n`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `issued before the date of assent to the Special Court (Trial of Offences Relating to Transactions in`
  line `Securities) Bill, 1992 by the President and where such notification, cancellation or order has been issued`
  line `on or after that date, within thirty days of the issuance of such notification, cancellation or order, as the`
  line `case may be; and the Special Court after hearing the parties, may make such order as it deems fit.`
  line `5. Establishment of Special Court. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, establish a Court to be called the Special Court.`
  line `( 2 ) The Special Court shall consist of 1 [one or more sitting Judges] of the High Court nominated by`
  line `the Chief Justice of the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the Special Court is`
  line `situated, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of India.`
  line `2 [( 3 ) When the office of 3 [a Judge of the Special Court] is vacant by reason of absence or leave, the`
  line `duties of the office shall be performed by such Judge of the High Court within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the Special Court is situated as the Chief Justice of that High Court may, with the concurrence`
  line `of the Chief Justice of India, nominate for the purpose and the Judge so appointed shall have all the`
  line `jurisdiction and powers of 3 [a Judge of the Special Court] including t he powers to pass final orders. ]`
  line `4 [ 5A. Distribution of cases amongst Judges of Special Court. — Where the Special Court consists`
  line `of two or more Judges, the Chief Justice of the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction`
  line `the Special Court is situated may, from time to time, by general or special order, make provisions as to the`
  line `distribution of cases amongst the Judges and specify the matters which may be dealt with by each of such`
  line Judge.]
  line `6. Cognizance of cases by Special Court. — The Special Court shall take cognizance of or try such`
  line `cases as are instituted before it or transferred to it as hereinafter provided.`
  line `7. Jurisdiction of Special Court. — Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, any`
  line `prosecution in respect of any offence referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 shall be instituted only in`
  line `the Special Court and any prosecution in respect of such offence pending in any court shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Special Court.`
  line `8. Jurisdiction of Special Court as to joint trials. — The Special Court shall have jurisdiction to try`
  line `any person concerned in the offence referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 either as a principal`
  line `conspirator or abettor and all other offences and accused persons as can be jointly tried therewith at one`
  line `trial in accordance with the Code.`
  line `9. Procedure and powers of Special Court. — ( 1 ) The Special Court shall, in the trial of such cases,`
  line `follow the procedure prescribed by the Code for the trial of warrant cases before a magistrate.`
  line `( 2 ) Save as expressly provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code shall, in so far as they are not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply to the proceedings before the Special Court and for the`
  line `purposes of the said provisions of the Code, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a Court of Session`
  line `and shall have all the powers of a Court of Session, and the person conducting a prosecution before the`
  line `Special Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
  line `( 3 ) The Special Court may pass upon any person convicted by it any sentence authorised by law for`
  line `the punishment of the offence of which such person is convicted.`
  line `( 4 ) While dealing with any other matter brought before it, the Special Court may adopt such`
  line `procedure as it may deem fit consistent with the principles of natural justice.`
  line `5 [ 9 A. Jurisdiction, powers, authority and procedure of Special Court in civil matters. — ( 1 ) On`
  line `and from the commencement of the Special Court (Trial of Offences Relating to Transactions in`
  line `Securities) Amendment Act, 1994 (24 of 1994) the Special Court shall exercise all such jurisdiction,`
  line `powers and authority as were exercisable, immediately before such commencement, by any civil court in`
  line `relation to any matter or claim —`
  line `( a ) relating to any property standing attached under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 3;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1997, s. 2 for “a sitting Judge” (w.e.f. 16 - 1 - 1997 ).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 24 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25 - 1 - 1994).`
  line `3. S ubs. by Act 6 of 1997, s. 2, for “the Judge of the Special Court ” (w.e.f. 16 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 16 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 24 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 25 - 1 - 1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
